Colombian Hostages Freed One Day After Kidnapping, RCN Reports

-- B y   R a n d a l l   W o o d s
-- 
2011-09-10T17:44:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-10/colombian-hostages-freed-one-day-after-kidnapping-rcn-reports.html
Gunmen today freed 24 boat
passengers on  Colombia ’s Pacific coast, one day after kidnapping
them in a possible robbery attempt,  RCN Radio  reported on its
website, citing Navy Admiral Hernando Wills.  Health officials are treating the passengers, many of whom
are suffering from dehydration, the  radio station reported .
Colombia’s Navy said yesterday in a  statement  that 15 people had
been kidnapped. The report said the boat was a local ferry, with
people transporting fish and groceries.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Woods in Santiago at 
 rwoods13@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Joshua Goodman  at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net . 